1
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:07,120
You'll never guess

2
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:08,119
how Min Shengquan's mother

3
00:00:08,119 --> 00:00:09,640
managed to find Lawyer Bai.

4
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:10,519
How did they meet?

5
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:11,480
Ruan Chen.

6
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:13,160
Min Shengquan's mother said

7
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:15,039
she met him while offering incense.

8
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:17,679
After Min Shengquan got into trouble,

9
00:00:17,839 --> 00:00:19,519
the guys from the bar came looking for her,

10
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,679
telling her to hire a lawyer.

11
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:22,440
So she reached out to Ruan Chen,

12
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:24,280
asking him to recommend a lawyer.

13
00:00:24,440 --> 00:00:27,879
Later, Ruan Chen dealt with Bai Qiming directly.

14
00:00:28,079 --> 00:00:29,480
His mother wasn't involved at all.

15
00:00:32,479 --> 00:00:33,799
That can't be a coincidence, right?

16
00:00:34,479 --> 00:00:36,280
Ruan Chen, like Luo Xiao,

17
00:00:36,479 --> 00:00:38,640
keeps popping up in this case way too often.

18
00:00:39,359 --> 00:00:41,280
Like a loose thread drifting in,

19
00:00:41,439 --> 00:00:42,439
we can't trace its source.

20
00:00:43,039 --> 00:00:45,240
We haven't dug deep enough.

21
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,000
If you're so good, you do it.

22
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:50,880
Everyone, put down what you're doing.

23
00:00:52,439 --> 00:00:53,799
Zhang Heng, come over here.

24
00:00:56,399 --> 00:00:57,640
Let me introduce you.

25
00:00:58,159 --> 00:01:00,880
This is the captain of the city economic crimes unit,

26
00:01:01,079 --> 00:01:01,920
Comrade Zhao Lin.

27
00:01:03,399 --> 00:01:05,840
And this is technician Comrade Gao Jie.

28
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:06,879
For the next little while,

29
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,760
they'll be stationed with our team,

30
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:11,760
mainly to investigate the Xin Qili case

31
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:14,439
and track down related leads.

32
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:16,480
We'll be in your care for a while.

33
00:01:18,319 --> 00:01:18,959
Zhang Heng,

34
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:21,719
you'll coordinate with the comrades from the city bureau.

35
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:25,239
Provide them with all the support and help we can.

36
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:28,000
So we can work together to crack this case soon.

37
00:01:44,959 --> 00:01:46,200
Take a moment to process this.

38
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,519
Because,

39
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,400
for you,

40
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,879
this is the door to a whole new world.

41
00:01:53,799 --> 00:01:55,120
Stepping through this door

42
00:01:56,879 --> 00:01:58,439
is truly not easy.

43
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,599
All this money...

44
00:02:03,079 --> 00:02:04,760
It was all laundered from Fengmao.

45
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,200
Right?

46
00:02:06,879 --> 00:02:07,719
Luo Xiao.

47
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:10,520
At its core, this world

48
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,520
doesn't run on rules.

49
00:02:14,599 --> 00:02:16,800
If this money were in a bank,

50
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,960
you wouldn't question its origin.

51
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,960
But sitting in this room,

52
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:24,159
you feel shocked, scared, and suspicious.

53
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,199
Why?

54
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:28,719
Because you're on the outside.

55
00:02:31,439 --> 00:02:32,599
You're a lawyer.

56
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:36,280
Well-versed in legal terms and frameworks.

57
00:02:36,719 --> 00:02:37,759
You know what kind of people

58
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:38,960
should do what kind of things.

59
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:39,919
Do it right,

60
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:42,240
and you're rewarded.

61
00:02:42,479 --> 00:02:43,520
Do it wrong,

62
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,159
and you're punished.

63
00:02:48,159 --> 00:02:49,159
So,

64
00:02:50,039 --> 00:02:51,879
you followed this set of rules,

65
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,479
made it out of the fishing village,

66
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:58,039
got into college, became a lawyer,

67
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,599
got married, and had kids.

68
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,599
But life

69
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:05,560
didn't go exactly as you expected,

70
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:08,280
handing you one sweet treat after another.

71
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,400
You're intimately familiar

72
00:03:11,039 --> 00:03:12,479
with loopholes at the edges of the rules.

73
00:03:13,199 --> 00:03:15,319
And you're quite proud of overturning many

74
00:03:15,319 --> 00:03:18,000
wrongdoers who should've been punished.

75
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,919
You believe

76
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,759
you can manipulate the rules of this world.

77
00:03:27,759 --> 00:03:28,719
Until

78
00:03:30,719 --> 00:03:32,280
Brother Mao died at your place.

79
00:03:33,639 --> 00:03:34,680
you got scared.

80
00:03:36,759 --> 00:03:37,719
Luo Xiao.

81
00:03:38,919 --> 00:03:40,680
Maybe you can skirt the edges

82
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,879
of laws and regulations.

83
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:44,479
But as for yourself,

84
00:03:45,639 --> 00:03:46,800
your decent job,

85
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,639
your happy family,

86
00:03:49,719 --> 00:03:50,479
your morality,

87
00:03:50,599 --> 00:03:51,520
your humanity,

88
00:03:51,719 --> 00:03:52,680
your dignity...

89
00:03:53,319 --> 00:03:55,560
are all spinning in the cage they built.

90
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:58,639
You spent too much time thinking about rules.

91
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:01,520
But in reality, they don't even exist.

92
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,439
Luo Xiao.

93
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:06,759
You want power.

94
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,919
You want freedom.

95
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,479
You want a billion.

96
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,879
You have a gift for changing the rules,

97
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:21,519
and courage that ordinary people lack.

98
00:04:22,319 --> 00:04:24,720
Money is just a tool,

99
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,360
but it can help

100
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,279
shine a light deep inside your heart

101
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,680
on your true desires,

102
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:32,680
instead of what this society

103
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,199
forces upon you.

104
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,279
Come.

105
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:41,399
Sit down and think it over.

106
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,480
Do you want

107
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:51,639
to keep living by these rules,

108
00:04:53,399 --> 00:04:54,240
or

109
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,439
embrace your own darkness

110
00:04:58,639 --> 00:04:59,519
and let it

111
00:05:00,639 --> 00:05:01,759
serve you?

112
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:15,279
One hundred and eighteen.

113
00:05:15,839 --> 00:05:16,920
Okay, all handed in.

114
00:05:28,839 --> 00:05:30,240
Doctor, how is the situation...

115
00:05:33,639 --> 00:05:34,959
As of right now,

116
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,639
the bone marrow function

117
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,800
and blood counts are relatively stable.

118
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:41,399
No significant signs of deterioration.

119
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,319
That's a positive sign.

120
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,399
However,

121
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,399
a county hospital like ours

122
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,399
has fairly limited treatment capabilities.

123
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:52,240
Things like the latest

124
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:53,879
international gene therapies,

125
00:05:54,279 --> 00:05:55,680
bone marrow transplants,

126
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:58,000
or cutting-edge targeted drugs,

127
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:02,079
you need a provincial or private hospital.

128
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:04,079
They have more resources.

129
00:06:05,519 --> 00:06:06,480
But,

130
00:06:07,079 --> 00:06:08,519
as I told you before,

131
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:12,639
follow-up treatment costs, medications,

132
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:15,720
and managing rejection reactions

133
00:06:15,839 --> 00:06:18,199
all add up to ongoing, hefty expenses.

134
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,040
You, as the family,

135
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,439
need to be mentally prepared.

136
00:06:24,319 --> 00:06:26,360
Well, doctor,

137
00:06:26,639 --> 00:06:28,800
roughly how much should we prepare?

138
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:33,519
That's hard for us to say.

139
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,120
It mainly depends on

140
00:06:35,199 --> 00:06:37,000
the child's physical condition

141
00:06:37,199 --> 00:06:39,240
and your family's financial situation

142
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,279
to determine a suitable treatment plan.

143
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,160
Okay.

144
00:06:45,319 --> 00:06:48,399
Well, thank you, doctor.

145
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,000
Thank you, doctor.

146
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:59,319
The provincial hospital is just too far.

147
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,279
I can't get away from work either.

148
00:07:01,439 --> 00:07:03,279
Maybe Mom should move there to help out.

149
00:07:04,319 --> 00:07:05,399
Let's not ask Mom to come.

150
00:07:05,399 --> 00:07:07,480
She's too old to be stressing over this.

151
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:11,600
That couple next to us at the provincial hospital,

152
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:12,879
they were from our area too.

153
00:07:13,079 --> 00:07:14,600
We exchanged contact info.

154
00:07:15,079 --> 00:07:16,519
They've moved back now.

155
00:07:16,959 --> 00:07:19,639
They said there's a private hospital here

156
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:22,639
with even better equipment than the provincial one.

157
00:07:23,079 --> 00:07:25,800
The only thing is, the cost

158
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:27,279
will definitely be much higher.

159
00:07:29,759 --> 00:07:32,040
How about we go check it out?

160
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:35,000
If it really comes to it,

161
00:07:37,439 --> 00:07:38,759
let's put the house up for sale.

162
00:07:38,839 --> 00:07:39,639
As for the money,

163
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,800
you don't need to worry.

164
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:41,759
I'll handle it.

165
00:07:43,079 --> 00:07:45,240
Let's use that 600,000 from last time first.

166
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,560
I've got another sum coming in soon.

167
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:52,079
Where would you get more money from?

168
00:07:53,279 --> 00:07:54,720
After Brother Mao's accident,

169
00:07:55,279 --> 00:07:56,879
Datou and I pooled some money

170
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:59,560
and bought some small Fengmao firms.

171
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,160
Now that things have blown over,

172
00:08:01,519 --> 00:08:03,160
once they're operating normally, revenue will return.

173
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:05,800
That's good then.

174
00:08:07,959 --> 00:08:09,480
You've been working so hard lately.

175
00:08:14,319 --> 00:08:15,480
What is money laundering?

176
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,879
It's taking illegally obtained funds

177
00:08:17,959 --> 00:08:20,560
through detailed, fake transactions

178
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:23,040
to turn them into seemingly legitimate income.

179
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,800
There are three steps.

180
00:08:25,279 --> 00:08:25,959
Placement.

181
00:08:26,519 --> 00:08:28,800
Putting illegal funds into the system.

182
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,959
For example, depositing cash

183
00:08:30,959 --> 00:08:32,480
into multiple different bank accounts,

184
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,879
purchasing high-value items,

185
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:36,360
or using fake import-export trade

186
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:37,440
to get the money on the books.

187
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,360
Fengmao Business Consulting Co., Ltd.

188
00:08:39,399 --> 00:08:41,399
is a classic case of split deposits,

189
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,960
breaking large sums into smaller amounts

190
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,720
and depositing them into various accounts.

191
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,559
Using what we call mule accounts.

192
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,159
This achieves the first step of laundering.

193
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:52,120
Let me lay out the specifics.

194
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:56,519
Ruan Chen has 30 million in clean money

195
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,919
That can serve as start-up capital.

196
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,879
But it can't solve the scale problem.

197
00:09:01,399 --> 00:09:03,399
The vast majority of the money is still overseas.

198
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,279
If we follow the standard

199
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:07,000
capital injection and investment rules,

200
00:09:07,919 --> 00:09:09,200
the entire cycle will take too long.

201
00:09:10,399 --> 00:09:12,320
Tedious paperwork, slow cycles,

202
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,639
and the risk is relatively high.

203
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,759
So it's not recommended.

204
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:17,480
So conventional methods won't work.

205
00:09:17,759 --> 00:09:21,039
Layering is splitting funds through multiple transfers,

206
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,000
to complicate the cash trail

207
00:09:23,159 --> 00:09:24,039
and confuse investigators.

208
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,639
So how do they pay the money?

209
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,600
Usually,

210
00:09:29,759 --> 00:09:31,080
they transfer through subsidiaries,

211
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:32,759
or use fake contracts as cover,

212
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,799
in the name of investment, spending, etc.

213
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:38,039
Of course, those contracts are all forged.

214
00:09:40,679 --> 00:09:41,840
And where does the money flow?

215
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:45,200
It can be R&D fees, tech purchasing fees,

216
00:09:45,679 --> 00:09:46,679
consulting fees, you name it,

217
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:47,679
technical services,

218
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:48,840
or raw material procurement.

219
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,200
In fact, it's all the same money,

220
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,759
just looping back around.

221
00:09:52,759 --> 00:09:53,799
Finally, integration.

222
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:56,440
The cleaned money, as legitimate income,

223
00:09:56,519 --> 00:09:58,200
returns to the criminals' hands.

224
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,840
Layer by layer on the books,

225
00:09:59,879 --> 00:10:01,000
splitting it across several layers,

226
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,720
before finally flowing back into our own hands,

227
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:04,159
appearing as a legitimate closed loop.

228
00:10:06,159 --> 00:10:09,039
So how do we transfer this money to Ruan Chen?

229
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,840
That's a billion, after all.

230
00:10:12,279 --> 00:10:13,639
Where does that much cash come from?

231
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,279
Underground banks.

232
00:10:15,679 --> 00:10:17,360
On the surface, they look like company offices,

233
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,440
but in reality,

234
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:20,440
they handle illegal money transactions,

235
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,080
cross-border transfers, and money laundering.

236
00:10:22,399 --> 00:10:24,039
Fengmao is one of the underground bank's

237
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,919
many downstream laundering channels.

238
00:10:26,679 --> 00:10:28,639
Bringing this money home is too risky.

239
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,399
So it has to stay overseas,

240
00:10:31,799 --> 00:10:34,360
and find a fund controlled by Ruan Chen,

241
00:10:34,679 --> 00:10:38,679
wiring the laundered money in as returns.

242
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,000
After Chen Yongjiang died,

243
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:44,120
Shengquan, downstream of Fengmao, got another payment.

244
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,480
But that money didn't flow back to Fengmao.

245
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:48,279
That's the portion you've been tracking.

246
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:49,879
Our analysis suggests

247
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:50,799
that someone has likely

248
00:10:50,879 --> 00:10:52,320
taken Chen Yongjiang's place,

249
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:54,559
restarting the whole chain.

250
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,039
Boss.

251
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,279
Call everyone back.

252
00:11:28,679 --> 00:11:29,519
Tell the boys,

253
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:30,799
Fengmao is back in business.

254
00:11:32,639 --> 00:11:33,480
Get ready to work.

255
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:34,799
You got it, bro.

256
00:11:46,519 --> 00:11:49,200
Master, this new Captain Zhao,

257
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:50,840
isn't she taking herself too seriously?

258
00:11:51,399 --> 00:11:52,600
Lecturing us the moment she arrives.

259
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:55,360
Outsiders always seem to know best.

260
00:11:55,759 --> 00:11:57,440
I'm long used to it.

261
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,639
Let's just wait and see

262
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,559
what she's really got.

263
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:22,799
Alright.

264
00:12:28,639 --> 00:12:29,440
I'll go park the car.

265
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:30,360
Okay.

266
00:12:39,039 --> 00:12:39,759
Feeling any better?

267
00:12:43,519 --> 00:12:45,720
There's a fruit basket someone sent over.

268
00:12:52,039 --> 00:12:53,799
From an old colleague.

269
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,559
Nothing to do with Brother Mao.

270
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,840
Zhang Heng really pissed me off.

271
00:13:00,879 --> 00:13:02,480
You can't fully blame your brother-in-law.

272
00:13:02,559 --> 00:13:03,360
I mean, someone called the police.

273
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,679
He had to respond, didn't he?

274
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,360
Why would they even call the cops?

275
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,559
Listen to this.

276
00:13:08,759 --> 00:13:10,519
The bank sent me to collect a debt.

277
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,559
For days I've been bringing a little stool,

278
00:13:12,559 --> 00:13:13,600
camping out at the guy's villa entrance.

279
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,399
When I finally got him to come out,

280
00:13:15,879 --> 00:13:16,840
he acts like a total scumbag.

281
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,879
Says he has no car and no house.

282
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,240
Can't pay back a thing.

283
00:13:20,679 --> 00:13:22,080
What a load of crap, right?

284
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:24,759
I've seen plenty of deadbeats,

285
00:13:24,879 --> 00:13:25,840
but one this self-righteous?

286
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:26,879
First time I've ever seen it.

287
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,080
Then he tries to leave.

288
00:13:28,279 --> 00:13:29,639
Obviously, I couldn't let him.

289
00:13:29,919 --> 00:13:32,240
I had my colleague grab his door handle,

290
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:33,840
and I yanked on his side mirror.

291
00:13:35,039 --> 00:13:35,720
But that piece-of-junk car,

292
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:37,000
god knows what quality it was,

293
00:13:37,159 --> 00:13:38,080
next thing I know,

294
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,519
I tore the thing right off.

295
00:13:41,159 --> 00:13:43,559
Don't push yourself so hard next time.

296
00:13:43,679 --> 00:13:44,519
If you got hurt,

297
00:13:44,519 --> 00:13:45,600
think about what you'd lose.

298
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:46,519
With your tiny salary,

299
00:13:46,519 --> 00:13:47,559
it wouldn't even cover medical bills.

300
00:13:48,559 --> 00:13:49,840
Wait, what kind of debt is this anyway?

301
00:13:49,879 --> 00:13:50,759
Sounds so dramatic.

302
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:51,960
What else? Bank loans.

303
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:54,080
Loans from years ago to losing businesses.

304
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:57,279
Back then a directive came down from above,

305
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:59,399
saying we had to develop new districts,

306
00:13:59,559 --> 00:14:00,519
and build industrial parks.

307
00:14:00,919 --> 00:14:02,559
The government kept pushing investment.

308
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:04,399
Companies swarmed in.

309
00:14:05,279 --> 00:14:06,639
If our bank refused to lend,

310
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,080
they'd say we were going against policy.

311
00:14:08,879 --> 00:14:09,559
And the result?

312
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:11,240
Some factories were just built,

313
00:14:11,519 --> 00:14:12,279
when the policy changed,

314
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:13,039
the subsidies got pulled,

315
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:13,960
environmental inspections came in,

316
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:14,919
and they all shut down.

317
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:16,600
Some had overcapacity,

318
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:17,919
and products that wouldn't sell,

319
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:19,360
so their cash flow broke.

320
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:20,720
The borrowers either ran away

321
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,879
or declared bankruptcy.

322
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:23,840
Some just flat-out refused to pay.

323
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,519
I mean, I'm a bank employee,

324
00:14:25,519 --> 00:14:26,919
and now I'm a door-to-door debt collector.

325
00:14:27,879 --> 00:14:30,240
Luo Xiao, if Fengmao were still around,

326
00:14:30,399 --> 00:14:31,519
I'd hand you my resume.

327
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:34,360
When they borrowed from the bank,

328
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,480
what about the collateral?

329
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:36,360
Collateral?

330
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,279
Those factories were all in the suburbs,

331
00:14:38,519 --> 00:14:40,159
their land paperwork a total mess,

332
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:42,279
and the machinery rusted into scrap metal.

333
00:14:42,399 --> 00:14:43,399
Who'd dare take that?

334
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:44,519
Auntie.

335
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:47,080
That's my burger.

336
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,480
No wonder it tasted so good.

337
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,440
It's fine, Auntie will buy you another one.

338
00:14:56,399 --> 00:14:57,759
You're so stingy.

339
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:58,879
Do you still want to eat

340
00:14:58,879 --> 00:15:00,600
Auntie's braised pork with chestnuts?

341
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,120
Stop pouting.

342
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,039
First, go to the county bank.

343
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,200
Find someone named Zhao Yaping.

344
00:15:08,879 --> 00:15:09,840
Tell her

345
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:11,480
we're a licensed

346
00:15:11,559 --> 00:15:13,240
private asset management company.

347
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,000
Tell her

348
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:18,240
we want to buy some non-performing assets.

349
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,159
I'm here to buy non-performing assets.

350
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:27,960
We don't have any.

351
00:15:29,159 --> 00:15:30,320
Yes, we do.

352
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:31,320
This way, please.

353
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:34,080
When selecting non-performing assets,

354
00:15:34,639 --> 00:15:37,039
make sure to pick the long-overdue bad debts.

355
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:40,039
These bad debts have dragged on for a long time,

356
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,960
so they're cheaper.

357
00:15:42,519 --> 00:15:43,840
Usually around ten percent of face value.

358
00:15:44,559 --> 00:15:45,320
Buy them up.

359
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:03,320
Brother Xiao.

360
00:16:05,159 --> 00:16:07,279
Once we've bought back this asset,

361
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:08,960
how do we collect the debt?

362
00:16:10,399 --> 00:16:12,000
Yaping told me

363
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:14,519
that this debtor, Chen Guang,

364
00:16:14,759 --> 00:16:15,919
invested in a fish farm.

365
00:16:16,559 --> 00:16:17,879
He borrowed six million in total.

366
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,440
In the end, the fish farm went under,

367
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,240
and he's been owing the money

368
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,759
for three or four years now.

369
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,879
Bro, deadbeats like him don't pay up easily.

370
00:16:29,399 --> 00:16:30,480
Want me to take a few of the boys

371
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:31,559
to scare him a bit?

372
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:33,600
The boys haven't worked in a while anyway.

373
00:16:34,559 --> 00:16:35,840
What we're going to do next

374
00:16:37,279 --> 00:16:38,320
is help him pay off his debt.

375
00:16:40,159 --> 00:16:40,919
Pay off his debt?

376
00:16:41,919 --> 00:16:42,639
Pay off his debt.
